    <node id="&quot;BOB CRATCHIT&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Bob Cratchit is Scrooge's clerk, a poor man with a large family, whose dwelling is blessed by the Spirit."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is Scrooge's clerk, who is underpaid and overworked, but remains cheerful and celebrates Christmas Eve."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is Scrooge's underpaid and overworked employee who is shocked when Scrooge raises his salary and promises to help his family."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is a cheerful and loving father who mourns the loss of his son Tiny Tim while maintaining a positive outlook for his family."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is a clerk to Ebenezer Scrooge and a central character in 'A Christmas Carol.'"&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is a mild-mannered man who defends Scrooge during the family's Christmas celebration, despite his wife's anger."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is a poor man whose family is affected by the death of another man, showing the social dynamics and economic struggles of the time."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is a recipient of Scrooge's newfound generosity, specifically mentioned in the context of sending a turkey."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is the father of the Cratchit family, who is joyful and caring, especially towards his son Tiny Tim."&lt;SEP&gt;"Bob Cratchit is the head of the Cratchit family, who leads the Christmas dinner celebration and expresses joy and gratitude."</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1d4b58de5429cd1261370c231c8673e8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9aac3484185ac66045df92214d245d5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b0f459f5af1c3a5e0b92cbe4ee48b77b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e2e7ebcc19a53b399dc03aded4743e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-503f0bfa5453467c7c61d160a3540eca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90b95db5c53e4364a6bee36b7aa4d70f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-83ac129dc9b56f84c46760d153d68e93&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-94bea83e7153fc2064aa382b494936a1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-19d72c57ae3408758b18d2568e86dc6b</data>
