      <data key="d1">"Marley is Scrooge's deceased business partner who returns as a ghost to warn Scrooge about his fate."&lt;SEP&gt;"Marley is Scrooge's deceased business partner, mentioned as having been dead for seven years."&lt;SEP&gt;"Marley is Scrooge's deceased business partner, whose ghostly face appears on the door knocker, hinting at his supernatural return."&lt;SEP&gt;"Marley is Scrooge's former business partner, referenced through 'Scrooge and Marley's' counting-house."&lt;SEP&gt;"Marley is referenced as a figure from Scrooge's past, associated with the hearth and winter seasons."&lt;SEP&gt;"Marley was Scrooge's business partner and sole friend, now deceased, whose ghost is central to the story."</data>
