    <node id="&quot;CHRISTMAS&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
      <data key="d1">"Christmas is a festive event celebrated by characters in the text, marked by singing, laughter, and good humor."&lt;SEP&gt;"Christmas is a time celebrated by Scrooge and the Cratchit family, symbolizing joy and transformation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Christmas is referenced in the decorations of the room above, symbolizing both joy and sorrow for the Cratchit family."&lt;SEP&gt;"Christmas is the event during which the family gathers, exchanges gifts, and enjoys each other's company, symbolizing warmth and togetherness."&lt;SEP&gt;"Christmas is the event during which the family scene takes place, involving presents and joy."&lt;SEP&gt;"Christmas is the festive occasion during which Scrooge's transformation and interactions take place."&lt;SEP&gt;"Christmas is the festive occasion during which the family gathers, plays games, and celebrates together."&lt;SEP&gt;"Christmas is the festive season being discussed, with Scrooge despising it while others celebrate its charitable spirit."&lt;SEP&gt;"Christmas is the festive season during which the interaction between Scrooge and the gentleman takes place, highlighting societal contrasts between abundance and want."&lt;SEP&gt;"Christmas is the holiday during which Fan brings Scrooge home, and it is a recurring theme in the text, symbolizing joy and family."&lt;SEP&gt;"Christmas is the holiday during which Scrooge's transformation occurs, leading to his generous actions and the celebration with Fred and Bob Cratchit."&lt;SEP&gt;"Christmas is the holiday during which the events take place, and it is condensed into the space of time Scrooge and the Spirit spend together."&lt;SEP&gt;"Christmas is the holiday that Scrooge dislikes, but his nephew and niece celebrate with laughter and good humor."&lt;SEP&gt;"Christmas is the time of year that triggers Scrooge's reflections and emotions, representing both joy and sorrow in his life."&lt;SEP&gt;"Christmas is the time of year when the events take place, including Fezziwig's ball and Scrooge's reflections."</data>
