    <node id="&quot;SCROOGE&quot;">
      <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
      <data key="d1">**Ebenezer Scrooge** is the central character in Charles Dickens' *A Christmas Carol*, initially depicted as a miserly, cold-hearted, and solitary old man who despises Christmas and human sympathy. He is a tight-fisted, covetous businessman, known for his lack of generosity and harsh treatment of his clerk, Bob Cratchit, as well as his disdain for his nephew and the poor. Scrooge is skeptical of festive cheer and charity, dismissing poverty with callous indifference.  

His transformation begins when he is visited by the ghost of his former business partner, Jacob Marley, who warns him of impending visits from three spirits. Throughout these supernatural encounters, Scrooge is forced to confront his past, present, and future. He revisits his lonely childhood, his apprenticeship under the jovial Fezziwig, and his gradual descent into greed and isolation. These reflections evoke deep regret, despair, and anxiety, particularly regarding missed opportunities for kindness.  

As the Ghost of Christmas Present shows him scenes of hardship—such as the Cratchit family’s struggles and Tiny Tim’s fate—Scrooge begins to show concern and remorse for his past indifference. The Ghost of Christmas Yet to Come reveals a bleak future, further horrifying him and solidifying his desire for change.  

By the story’s end, Scrooge undergoes a profound transformation, shedding his miserly ways to embrace generosity, joy, and compassion. He becomes kind-hearted, aiding the Cratchits, reconciling with his nephew, and celebrating the spirit of Christmas. His journey illustrates redemption, proving that even the most hardened individuals can change through self-reflection and empathy.</data>
      <data key="d2">chunk-43c9bee23adfa77aa9dedd22401bba7d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91572b3cd42786ba4cb2f180ca25cbf4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-54bdd22db1f84a965b5f4c06c9216d8d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b0f459f5af1c3a5e0b92cbe4ee48b77b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90b95db5c53e4364a6bee36b7aa4d70f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b2f98bc7abb0c67d4c86055c7fd72218&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-da2472b4ef2a535b62908f14d0fb0ca9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8590d9263cd2cd4fa583c432fc54e6c3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91614df5cb74cbe5e109a338a82041e9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6c248858d1b13ab7ee9ca13c1aeed6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb661c37436355ccec2769b1d0350c5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-02baee20cc9463dbe08170a8e1043e32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89777b838d5447c7bd1ec11282c4ee89&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9aac3484185ac66045df92214d245d5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c7b10789a9cb0af6c553730b29bd9034&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-99b0ec7f7e006561352b5d65e849611d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90d5764e301321c087f5a8f78b73a145&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-773d0df1dd25c356f7b771d780583e09&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f1a4fbcf1ed86864b9bfd5e8dba4c683&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-74e2466de2f67fd710ef2f20c0a8d9e0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-503f0bfa5453467c7c61d160a3540eca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e1f29eeadc1d8ab46dc8a0bbd3c56b64&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-19d72c57ae3408758b18d2568e86dc6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8f738cb25d60a7dab782162d9d0a25ed&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-60fc063c79fc0d4acc91a57e79de04dc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5dac41b3f9eeaf794f0147400b1718cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-83ac129dc9b56f84c46760d153d68e93&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-94bea83e7153fc2064aa382b494936a1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bb21d58d36c6306fd8810ddd51c4a971&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-359187e7571bda4b0b08b2e0b6581e52&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-843b5b2f944c7413d9ca876e2e2f151f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1aa50206d02ed89418f65f97c6441d1c</data>
