      <data key="d4">75.0</data>
      <data key="d5">"Christmas is a significant event in Scrooge's past, associated with family and joy."&lt;SEP&gt;"Christmas is the setting for Scrooge's transformation and participation in family activities."&lt;SEP&gt;"Christmas triggers Scrooge's reflections and emotions, highlighting his loneliness and regret."&lt;SEP&gt;"Scrooge despises Christmas and rejects its traditions and charitable spirit."&lt;SEP&gt;"Scrooge dislikes Christmas and refuses to participate in the celebrations."&lt;SEP&gt;"Scrooge experiences the essence of Christmas through the scenes shown by the Spirit, leading to his transformation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Scrooge vows to honor Christmas, symbolizing his change of heart."&lt;SEP&gt;"Scrooge's disdain for Christmas and its charitable traditions is evident in his refusal to contribute to the poor during the season."&lt;SEP&gt;"Scrooge's transformation and actions are centered around the Christmas event."&lt;SEP&gt;"Scrooge's transformation is centered around Christmas, and he learns to celebrate the holiday with generosity and joy."</data>
